Review: Pretty good Thai restaurant and liked the vibe at the place. Got my classic chicken drunken noodles and Thai iced tea and had no complaints!

Got the Quesadilla here and they were pretty good but like $11 and advertised as an appetizer. Came here for Monday Trivia (which our team won) which was pretty cool and organized. Chill vibes all around and good service
Got the quesabrilla and it was pretty good! Meat became kinda dry after a while but food was pretty good. Sat outdoors and the vibes were pretty nice as well. Food came out pretty fast as well

Came here with a lot of friends to get them Ethiopian food for the first time and everyone seemed to love it! All the classic and main options were there and the staff was super helpful in helping us determine what to get and how much to get. This was the first time that many of my friends had tried Ethiopian food and everyone really seemed to enjoy and eat a lot. Make sure to go with a group of people to be able and try multiple things
Food was great and service was excellent. Had the all you can eat buffet (which was $33) but the food was really good and I would definitely go back again
First time having ice cream at this place and was pretty good! Got the salty caramel and wild berry lavender flavors which were both solid tastes. Staff was also nice!

This might be a hot take but Boylan has always been my favorite place to get burgers. The build your own burger, milkshakes, and curly fries have always been a classic combination and the food tastes great. Every time I’m at Cville Boylan is always a spot I try to go to

BEST. DUMPLINGS. EVER.

Literally one of my favorite places at YVA. My go-to is pork dumplings, noodles, and fried rice and it hits every time. Plus they have boba tea which is always a great drink to have. If you’re in the UVA area ever, this is a must have
Good gelato; good service. Great place to grab gelato and share with friends! There was a line for this place even near closing
Got the classic drunken noodles and Thai ice teas and they were pretty good! Got the food as takeout and quality did not go down

Drunken noodles were really bomb! Thai tea was an L though - was mostly just ice. Also, music was loud which made hearing other people difficult but the atmosphere was immaculate other than that. Great service too

Got the BBQ Pork chops here and they were so delicious! Also, this place gives popcorn out as a free snack before your food which is super original (and I may have gone crazy with the old bay). Rating this a 4 instead of a 5 because food was a bit pricey and we got seated next to their live singer outside which made talking difficult
